additionalInfo.description:
Rules validates an Australia Health Identifier (IHI number -Individual Health Care, HPI-I Healthcare Provider Identifier - Individual (HPI-I) - and HPO-O -Healthcare Provider Identifier - Organization (HPI-O) after checking the length and the format . Health Identifiers numbers are a 16 digit string. 

Formats validated: 1111-1111-1111-1111 or 1111 1111 1111 1111 or 1111111111111111

Tags: Validity, Health, Australia
Removes all punctuation symbols and character spaces from an input field, and returns the remaining digits and letters.

Mapplet applies the Luhn algorithm, a mod 10 calculation commonly used for Credit Card number check digit validation, to an input value.
Returns Valid if the supplied check digit matches the calculated value, Invalid if not.
